<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1005] Tests are ignored when using dependenciesToScan on linux only</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1005</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When building on Windows 7 64 bit I can&apos;t see any problem.&lt;br/&gt;
When running on linux my tests aren&apos;t running, or at least don&apos;t get reported.&lt;br/&gt;
I am using the same project on 2 machines.&lt;br/&gt;
I am using the feature described in: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-569&quot; title=&quot;There should be a way to run unit tests from a dependency jar.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-569&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-569&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;{{{&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;plugin&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;maven-surefire-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;2.15&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
					&amp;lt;dependenciesToScan&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
						&amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;my.group:myArtifact&amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
					&amp;lt;/dependenciesToScan&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
					&amp;lt;argLine&amp;gt;-DbaseClassesPath=${project.build.directory}${file.separator}classes&amp;lt;/argLine&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;/plugin&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;		&amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;my.group&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;myArtifact&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;version&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;type&amp;gt;test-jar&amp;lt;/type&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;scope&amp;gt;test&amp;lt;/scope&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;}}}&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
