                            <comment id="14457009" author="galusben@gmail.com" created="Sat, 15 Jun 2013 05:52:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was that the name of the test class did not have Test in it.&lt;br/&gt;
For some reason  that did not work on linux, but work fine on windows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455837" author="agudian" created="Sat, 15 Jun 2013 07:40:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would you mind creating a small sample project to demonstrate the issue? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14457008" author="galusben@gmail.com" created="Sat, 15 Jun 2013 10:00:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for taking a look.&lt;br/&gt;
Added sample_project.zip - to demonstrate the problem.&lt;br/&gt;
After some more investigation, i see that the problem is that on windows, if i have a package named test, the class in it is getting scanned for tests. On linux it is not getting scanned.&lt;br/&gt;
So, the issue is that you will get different tests running on linux and windows.&lt;br/&gt;
In sample_project.zip I gave the output of running mvn clean install on windows and linux.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks again!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455954" author="krosenvold" created="Sun, 16 Jun 2013 07:01:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems like a bug, even though your problem &quot;solved&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455917" author="agudian" created="Sun, 16 Jun 2013 14:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yepp, verified it on windows. I&apos;ll take this one, I guess... &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
